Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.60,0:01:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The archangels, which we've mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.59,0:01:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate 50,000 up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.42,0:01:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these numbers, if you remember, are logarithmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.26,0:01:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,50,000, 10 times 10 times 10, 50,000 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.79,0:01:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a comparable,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.20,0:01:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,these are only ways of speaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.59,0:01:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of the power of an archangel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.70,0:01:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A passing thought of an archangel
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.23,0:01:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is enough to blow you out for 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.20,0:01:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes 30 years to figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.84,0:01:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,how to describe what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.70,0:02:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A passing thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.92,0:02:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so there are other descriptions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.85,0:02:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ultimate spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.36,0:02:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha nature, as allness, as void.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.40,0:02:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Native American Great Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.81,0:02:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 850, which is way up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.62,0:02:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yehwah, I'm not familiar with,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.03,0:02:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah, I'm not too familiar with,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.65,0:02:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but they were there, so I did them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.65,0:02:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yehwah was 460, Jehovah was 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.12,0:02:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there are other ways of describing gods
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.40,0:02:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.71,0:02:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we just thought we would see what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.52,0:02:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't say that I understand all of these either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.37,0:02:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a term there, Elohim,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.16,0:02:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which I don't know what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.09,0:02:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,God of the Old Testament is 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.00,0:02:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Greek gods are 90,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.25,0:02:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Germanic gods, Scandinavian gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.31,0:02:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So what would you conclude from all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.12,0:02:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That these were very primitive,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.78,0:03:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,tribal cultures, very primitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.59,0:03:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.78,0:03:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The other gods that have been worshipped over time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.18,0:03:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the gods of war,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.24,0:03:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,pagan gods of Rome,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.96,0:03:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the names for God,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.59,0:03:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of God as Om,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.71,0:03:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as Aum,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.80,0:03:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or Mother-Father God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.34,0:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother-Father God makes your own go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.56,0:03:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't project gender onto an infinite reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.09,0:03:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's giving politics a little too far, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.55,0:03:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't project gender onto the infinite reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.56,0:03:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You like trying to project gender onto electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.08,0:03:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.56,0:03:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond all gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.18,0:03:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we go to the great spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.12,0:04:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They, characteristically, have calibrated it at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.86,0:04:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus the Christ, a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.28,0:04:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha, a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna, Zoroaster, the twelve Christian apostles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.28,0:04:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the greats of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.21,0:04:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and there may be some I have forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.21,0:04:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And if so, you can put them on a three-by-five card
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.47,0:04:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave them with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.47,0:04:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As it is, we spent months and years at this already,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.36,0:04:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can leave some, but you don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.86,0:04:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought first we'll start with the verifiable reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.22,0:04:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if everything on the first slide was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.54,0:04:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You have permission to ask in front of this audience, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.18,0:04:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything on the first slide was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.38,0:04:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything on the first slide was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.50,0:04:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So we check ourself as we go, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.50,0:05:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We check ourself as we go,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.22,0:05:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because the best of intentions, through ignorance,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.22,0:05:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,one can make a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.72,0:05:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't want the karma of making a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.72,0:05:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as a spiritual teacher with an audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.72,0:05:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, the twelve Christian apostles then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that in the first century,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.57,0:05:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,first century Christianity is extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.57,0:05:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The twelve Christian apostles at 980,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.50,0:05:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you remember the Holy Spirit was transmitted to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.67,0:05:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In the form of the Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.67,0:05:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of the Christ energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.67,0:05:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which is coming from God through that avatar,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.41,0:05:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,was transmitted to the apostles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.41,0:05:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you look at twelve people,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.41,0:05:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that's such a profound effect on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.41,0:05:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They must have been carrying some energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And as it turned out, 980, John the Baptist,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.79,0:05:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Peter, Saul of Tarsus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.74,0:06:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was Saul of Tarsus and he became St. Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.74,0:06:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.00,0:06:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We got Paul instead of Saul?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.87,0:06:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not much of a biblical scholar, as you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.62,0:06:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I meant to tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.62,0:06:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,these are not the corrected slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.62,0:06:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the first run.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.11,0:06:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we go back to them and we make the corrections.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.11,0:06:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are some things I had to write in and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.11,0:06:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I missed that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.11,0:06:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll get that one before it gets published in a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.11,0:06:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're running it through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.30,0:06:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll pick up anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.52,0:06:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's really annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.52,0:06:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time you write a book,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.52,0:06:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to go back and correct this,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.52,0:06:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you reprint it, and then you correct that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.52,0:06:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and then somebody writes you something missing on that page.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.52,0:06:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So this time, we're going to do it all in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.52,0:06:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.52,0:06:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Abraham, Moses,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.17,0:07:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so the great avatars of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.22,0:07:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Muhammad is a peculiar case at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.25,0:07:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He dictated in the Quran.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.29,0:07:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He was at 740.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.29,0:07:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Later in life, he took up the sword,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.27,0:07:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way of the sword,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.27,0:07:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and his calibrated energy dropped to 135.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.94,0:07:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's all phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.81,0:07:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,not peculiar to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.81,0:07:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but demonstrated most vividly by him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.45,0:07:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, they took up the sword
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.22,0:07:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and began killing infidels,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.22,0:07:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,which has continued to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.37,0:07:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you get off the rail
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.25,0:07:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,without kinesiology, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.97,0:07:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That may have something to do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.43,0:07:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with the way we calibrated North Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.43,0:07:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,between plus 10 and plus 40 latitude north,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.17,0:08:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's predominantly Islamic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.81,0:08:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.74,0:08:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we've seen this phenomena happen in many others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.74,0:08:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a separate section of the book
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.60,0:08:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of still honored gurus,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.37,0:08:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,who at one time were quite high,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.37,0:08:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and now are considerably less than 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.12,0:08:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We've spoken of that before,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.12,0:08:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that as consciousness evolves,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.81,0:08:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,there are certain challenges that come up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.77,0:08:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And unless one has been adequately informed beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.77,0:08:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,one is not prepared for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.50,0:08:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, I have tried to consistently mention
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and describe the pitfalls,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.58,0:08:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,how they came in,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.91,0:08:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and what the error is,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.91,0:08:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because the error sounds very convincing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.90,0:08:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What the error was,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.90,0:08:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I never had the chance to research it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.90,0:08:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that came to Muhammad,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.90,0:09:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that he bought into.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.53,0:09:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably bought that he was saving them for God,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.53,0:09:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,probably something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.84,0:09:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he thought that by killing them,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he was honoring God, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.12,0:09:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as we mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.04,0:09:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to God is through joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.04,0:09:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not through death and destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.04,0:09:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you're for chocolate,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.26,0:09:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to kill vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.98,0:09:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably thought you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.20,0:09:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Such fall in grace has happened
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.51,0:09:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with a lot of well-known names in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.51,0:09:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's also happened in the secular domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,not just spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.51,0:09:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.05,0:09:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.28,0:09:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think calibrated around 450
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.28,0:09:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,when he wrote Mon Confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.28,0:09:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Early political world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.28,0:09:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he was about 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.28,0:09:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.28,0:09:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he was like 90 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.96,0:10:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Napoleon was very advanced consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.96,0:10:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a brilliant genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he calibrated around 455, 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.44,0:10:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And after he crowned himself emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.44,0:10:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he crashed and before he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.44,0:10:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,he was like 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.15,0:10:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At Waterloo,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.98,0:10:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the English,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Wellington, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wellington calibrated at 460
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.25,0:10:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time of Waterloo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.38,0:10:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And by that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.38,0:10:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,he had fallen to I think about 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.25,0:10:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.25,0:10:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.25,0:10:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it has happened to other people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.25,0:10:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,who reach a certain level of,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.30,0:10:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, power over others.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.30,0:10:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.50,0:10:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,there comes a temptation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.78,0:10:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the error of judgment is made
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.85,0:10:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and because the person is not adequately prepared in advance,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.85,0:10:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they fall for the sophistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.97,0:11:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,God created sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.97,0:11:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sex is good,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.97,0:11:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so let's all have group sex and worship God.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.97,0:11:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.61,0:11:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's groups like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.61,0:11:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They were recently famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.61,0:11:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That group crashed very amazingly not long ago too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.40,0:11:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.50,0:11:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the unprepared mind then is susceptible to error.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.57,0:11:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.60,0:11:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,again,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.60,0:11:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what was the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.60,0:11:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem was ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.62,0:11:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one ignorance
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.62,0:11:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is that the human mind cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.36,0:11:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind cannot know truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.36,0:11:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,At a certain level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.36,0:11:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual truth is intuitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.36,0:11:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it comes to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:11:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll recognize its falsity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.10,0:11:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.10,0:11:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for other reasons I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.22,0:11:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a person can fall for it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.32,0:11:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore we try to prepare everybody in advance for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.32,0:11:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We tell them,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.86,0:11:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,then as you get into the 500s
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.86,0:12:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where everybody is beautiful, holy, and innocent,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.86,0:12:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are wide open on the downside
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.27,0:12:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to be taken in by
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.27,0:12:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the con men of spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.27,0:12:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.27,0:12:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,so let's go on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.17,0:12:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.17,0:12:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.17,0:12:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we wanted to calibrate some of the world's religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.17,0:12:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is stuff I've all gotten in the mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.17,0:12:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's asking all these questions endlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.46,0:12:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and asked when is this book going to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.46,0:12:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is subject to change and verification later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.62,0:12:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.37,0:12:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.37,0:12:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level of mankind is always shifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.37,0:12:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.37,0:12:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A religious sect or something may calibrate here today
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.37,0:12:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and make a big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.37,0:12:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A mistake can drop like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.37,0:12:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Or they may suddenly throw out some falsity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.37,0:12:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly rise like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.46,0:12:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So it should really have a date on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.46,0:12:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is of recent times.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.46,0:12:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometime in the early part of the summer or over the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.90,0:12:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mahayana Buddhism seems to have survived the best
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.90,0:13:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of any of the religions as far as
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.90,0:13:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,being desecrated by extraneous error.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.38,0:13:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Of which Zen Buddhism is a form of Mahayana Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.41,0:13:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinayana Buddhism is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.41,0:13:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the way of the individual enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.41,0:13:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mahayana is the greater vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.74,0:13:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That one stays back as a bodhisattva because
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.02,0:13:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of one's love and devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.02,0:13:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,for the consciousness of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.10,0:13:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of Manahayana is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.76,0:13:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the enlightenment of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.76,0:13:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as our prayers
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.83,0:13:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,are for the enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for the emergence of life energy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.83,0:13:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and the downtrodden of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.83,0:13:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So to do that, holding in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.83,0:13:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,those who are at the very bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.83,0:13:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,who have given up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.25,0:13:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,almost depleted of the energy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.25,0:13:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So we as a group do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.25,0:13:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's characteristic of Mahayana.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.25,0:13:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinayana, you worry about your own enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.50,0:14:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You just worry about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.29,0:14:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mahayana, you hold all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.58,0:14:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotus Land Buddhism we mentioned this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.99,0:14:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is somewhat like, in my understanding of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.99,0:14:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is somewhat like Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.99,0:14:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,See, if the gravity, the spiritual gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.40,0:14:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of this world is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.40,0:14:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's unlikely you're going to really reach
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.40,0:14:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a great height here because of the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.40,0:14:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,profound negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.40,0:14:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,One should strive for something that's realizable
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.69,0:14:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,such as unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.38,0:14:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and at death one automatically goes into
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.38,0:14:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a celestial realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.94,0:14:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha says somewhat, or some branch of Buddhism
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.10,0:14:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.10,0:14:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of heaven is called Lotus Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.10,0:14:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So here one earns merit, perfects oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.28,0:14:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the Buddha acts as,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.61,0:15:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so Christ is your intercessor in heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.61,0:15:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Buddha of the Lotus Land
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.61,0:15:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,who has a Sanskrit name that I can remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the name of the Buddha of the Lotus Land?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.30,0:15:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.65,0:15:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyhow, acts as your, speaks for you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.82,0:15:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Lotus Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.82,0:15:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotus Land is really heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.82,0:15:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.82,0:15:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's saying most of humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.82,0:15:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you can shoot for Lotus Land
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.08,0:15:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and from there the presence of the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.08,0:15:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,will carry you through to enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.87,0:15:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is a great similarity then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.07,0:15:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in Lotus Land Buddhism and Christian heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.13,0:15:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tantric Buddhism calibrates considerably less
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,because it gets involved in occult
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.29,0:15:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and esoteric form.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.38,0:15:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets involved in form
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.49,0:15:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and manipulations of form and symbolism.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.49,0:15:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's considerably less powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:16:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there are very interpretations
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.54,0:16:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which are quite recent of one Buddhism
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.54,0:16:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and we wondered how they calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.05,0:16:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrated in the 400s
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.05,0:16:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so that an intelligent person can read this
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.05,0:16:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and get what it's at.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.45,0:16:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And a person who really gets what it's at
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.45,0:16:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.63,0:16:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and move beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.63,0:16:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that which they've just read.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.63,0:16:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the teaching says move this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.74,0:16:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they read and they read and they read
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.74,0:16:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they get,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.74,0:16:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, how better is that moving this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.74,0:16:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you got to come off the page,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.74,0:16:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,come out of the book
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.74,0:16:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and experience the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.05,0:16:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity beginning in the first century
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.53,0:16:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates extremely high, 980.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.90,0:16:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.90,0:16:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.90,0:16:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it right here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.25,0:16:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.25,0:16:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't see that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.84,0:16:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Get dehydrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.58,0:16:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning Christianity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.58,0:16:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,was really called the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.71,0:17:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,As we see, the apostles calibrated at 980.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.89,0:17:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And interestingly enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.89,0:17:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,first century Christianity calibrates at 980,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.90,0:17:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly that of the apostles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.90,0:17:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity took a giant fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.82,0:17:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It crashed worse than any other religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.27,0:17:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,At the Council of Nicaea,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.27,0:17:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it dropped from the 900s
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.27,0:17:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,down to 465, 485, somewhere in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.75,0:17:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That in itself is a whole research project.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.75,0:17:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was at this council?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.17,0:17:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What were the factions involved?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.17,0:17:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the energy that brought it down?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.17,0:17:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the spiritual error?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.17,0:17:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the sacrifice that was made?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.79,0:17:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My suspicion is that for political reasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.79,0:17:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,some sacrifice in truth was made.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.79,0:17:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can't condemn it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.66,0:17:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because maybe in order to survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.66,0:17:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity had to make that concession,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.66,0:17:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps politically.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.66,0:18:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's sort of my intuition,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.66,0:18:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are certain points
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.89,0:18:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at which certain religions
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.89,0:18:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,have had to make some kind of an accord
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.89,0:18:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with the political powers that ruled at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.89,0:18:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to survive at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.89,0:18:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they said,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.21,0:18:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it's better to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.21,0:18:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and give up, let's say, the requirement
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.58,0:18:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to not eat meat on Friday or something trivial
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.58,0:18:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and survive rather than insist on it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.58,0:18:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and find ourselves outlawed and executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.72,0:18:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.42,0:18:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So first century Christianity then reflects
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.42,0:18:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the apostles at 980,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.51,0:18:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the dominance of spiritual truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.65,0:18:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and something happened to it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.74,0:18:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,after the Council of Nicaea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.74,0:18:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The College of Cardinals right now
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.61,0:18:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 490.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.61,0:18:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The papacy itself, as a position,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.61,0:18:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 570,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.61,0:18:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the same as the Dalai Lama,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.61,0:18:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,who, see, those two functions are similar,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.61,0:19:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to be head of a church.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.51,0:19:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of these calibrations you have to,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.51,0:19:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, we're not talking about judgmentalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.90,0:19:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,One is not better than another.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.90,0:19:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because each calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.90,0:19:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is suitable for itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.90,0:19:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So perfect doesn't mean higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.50,0:19:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It means perfect for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.50,0:19:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At 570, you would make a very bad
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.50,0:19:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,president of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.50,0:19:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600, it'd be a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.09,0:19:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The ideal president of the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.09,0:19:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,would be around 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.09,0:19:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the presidents, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.09,0:19:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,have been around that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.22,0:19:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Higher than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.22,0:19:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd rather be a professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.22,0:19:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower than that, you haven't got the savvy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.22,0:19:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to ask yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.18,0:19:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what's ideal?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.18,0:19:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To be ideal as the inspirational head
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.18,0:19:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of a world church,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.18,0:19:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you should calibrate around 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.18,0:19:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And, peculiarly enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.54,0:19:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.54,0:20:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The current pope is at 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.38,0:20:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Dalai Lama,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.67,0:20:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,about the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.67,0:20:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Coptic, I'm not that familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.33,0:20:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Born again is more sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.33,0:20:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a radical positionality to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.33,0:20:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So it drops down to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.33,0:20:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a us and them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.14,0:20:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.14,0:20:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of an us and them about it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.14,0:20:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The agnostics
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.74,0:20:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't calibrate as high as I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.74,0:20:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,they would, and I would,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.74,0:20:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have to research it further.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.22,0:20:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I was,
